The macro metal_unused(x) expands to (x) = (x); and in metal_sys_init it is used as metal_unused(params); which becomes params = params; This performs an assignment to the parameter variable 'params' (i.e. modifies the pointer itself), so a function parameter is being modified and Rule 17.8 is violated.
</scenario>

